HEADWORD: Chevrotain
<hw>Chev`ro*tain"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>chevrotin</ets>, OF. <ets>chevrot</ets> little goat, roe, dim. of
<ets>chevre</ets> goat. See <er>Chevron</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small ruminant of the family <fam>Tragulid⟦ae⟧</fam> a allied to
the musk deer. It inhabits Africa and the East Indies. See
<er>Kanchil</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

